The 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic is an ongoing disease pandemic by coronavirus 2019 (COVID-19), caused by coronavirus 2 of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS-CoV-2).
The outbreak was identified in Wuhan, China, in December 2019, as a public health emergency of international importance on 30 January 2020, and recognized as a pandemic on 11 March 2020.
