Hong Kong recommends using a surgical mask to take public transport or to be in crowded places.
Thailand's health officials recommend that people make fabric masks in their homes and wash them daily.
The Czech Republic and Slovakia banned exiting public spaces without wearing a mask or without covering their nose and mouth.
On March 16, Vietnam requested that all people wear a mask while in public spaces to protect themselves and others.
The Austrian Government demanded the use of masks by all persons entering a supermarket.
Israel requested that all residents wear masks in public.
Taiwan, which has manufactured 10 million masks a day since mid-March, on 1 April demanded the use of masks by passengers on long-distance trains and buses.
